subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Females recognised by colour patterns on body (
Fig. 26
); differ from other species which may have similar abdominal patterns by slightly larger lateral eyes which are situated closer to PME; epigyne with atrium rim teardrop-shaped, small flap posteriorly; small intromittent orifices open antero-laterally (
Fig. 67
). Male dark with pale legs, femora I and II may have dark infuscated bands (
Fig. 28
); RTA with long slender tip directed laterally with slight curve anteriorly (
Fig. 65
); VTA slender (
Fig. 66
).
